  "subject": "Update kubespray version to 2.14.1",
  "commit_message": "Update kubespray version to 2.14.1\n\n- Replace move of ansible.cfg from kubespray distribution to\n  /etc/ansible with ANSIBLE_CONFIG environment variable.  Ansible\n  modifies ansible.cfg during installation, and the paths in it are\n  relative.\n\n- Set ansible_python_interpreter explicitly to python3.  This prevents\n  \"UNREACHABLE /usr/bin/python not found\" errors.\n\n- kubespray 2.14.1 requires a kubernetes version > 1.16.  Bump the\n  version to 1.17.12.\n\n- kubespray 2.14.1 replaces helm 2 with helm 3.  This removes support\n  for helm serve.  Replace serve steps in emco charts with file\n  relative URLs.\n\n- helm 3 also removes support for helm init.  It is no longer\n  necessary to call this.\n\n- Helm deploy of emco failed due to nil\n  PersistentVolume.metadata.labels.type.  Add storageType: hostPath to\n  etcd/values.yaml.\n\n- emco-fluentd pod stuck in CrashLoopBackOff due to failure to resolve\n  cluster.local name.  The cluster name comes from the Provisioning\n  object.  Explicitly set the fluentd.clusterDomain value during helm\n  install.\n\n- Ignore 404 when deleting non-existent project in emco.sh test.\n\n- Fix typo in deployments/helm/v2/emco/Chart.yaml.\n\nIssue-ID: MULTICLOUD-1230\nSigned-off-by: Todd Malsbary <todd.malsbary@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I66ff2549b585b83f3560d12734244f044a180976\n",
